# CLI Module

The CLI module extends the baseline project with a [Typer](https://typer.tiangolo.com/) command suite
powered by Loguru for structured output.

## Enabling the Module

Set the Copier prompt `cli_module=enabled` when rendering the template:

```bash
copier copy . my-project --data '{"cli_module": "enabled"}'
```

This scaffolds `src/{{ project_slug }}/cli/` with the `Typer` application and wires smoke tests into
`tests/test_cli.py`.

## Validation Commands

Run the smoke tests locally before committing:

```bash
uv run python -m {{ package_name }}.cli --help
uv run pytest tests/test_cli.py
```

The `quickstart` command delegates to `run_quickstart(dry_run=...)`, providing the same automation as
the baseline script with richer logging.

## CI Integration

The module catalog exposes a `cli-smoke` job. Replicate this locally with:

```bash
uv run pytest tests/test_cli.py -k quickstart
```

When `shared_logic=enabled`, the CLI automatically enriches its output with summaries from
`shared.logic`.
